{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bd0d29ab-f970-4b73-ae8f-7262f0eef146","content":"Here's the plan and architecture for adding RAG-based Q&A to your .NET 10 Web API:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐       ┌────────────────┐\n│  POST /ingest│──────▶│ Chunking Pipeline │──────▶│ Vector Store   │\n│              │       │ (Markdown→Chunks) │       │ (embeddings)   │\n└──────────────┘       └──────────────────┘       └────────────────┘\n                                                          │\n┌──────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐              ▼\n│  POST /ask   │──────▶│  Query Pipeline   │◀─── similarity search\n│  { question }│       │  Retrieve + LLM   │───▶ grounded answer\n└──────────────┘       └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Components\n\n### 1. Document Ingestion (`POST /ingest`)\n- Scans `Docs/*.md` files\n- **Chunking strategy**: split by markdown heading (`#`, `##`) first, then apply a sliding-window token limit (~300 tokens per chunk, ~50-token overlap) for sections that exceed the limit\n- Each chunk stores: `id`, `source file`, `heading path`, `text`, `embedding vector`\n\n### 2. Embedding & Vector Store\n- Use **Microsoft.Extensions.AI** abstraction with an OpenAI-compatible embedding model (e.g., `text-embedding-3-small`)\n- Store vectors in an **in-memory** vector store for simplicity (swap to Qdrant/pgvector/Azure AI Search later)\n- Consider the **Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData** package (preview) for a provider-agnostic store interface\n\n### 3. Query Endpoint (`POST /ask`)\n- Embed the user's question\n- Retrieve top-K (k=3–5) chunks by cosine similarity\n- Build a prompt: system instructions + retrieved chunks + user question\n- Call an LLM (e.g., GPT-4o via `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI`) to generate an answer grounded in the chunks\n- Return: `{ answer, sources[] }`\n\n### 4. Recommended NuGet Packages\n| Purpose | Package |\n|---------|---------|\n| LLM/embedding abstraction | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` |\n| OpenAI provider | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI` |\n| Vector data abstraction | `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` |\n| In-memory vector store | `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.InMemory` |\n| Markdown parsing (chunking) | `Markdig` |\n\n### 5. Project Structure (proposed)\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Docs/                        # existing markdown docs\n├── Models/\n│   ├── DocumentChunk.cs         # chunk data model\n│   └── AskRequest/Response.cs\n├── Services/\n│   ├── DocumentIngestionService.cs\n│   ├── ChunkingService.cs\n│   └── RagQueryService.cs\n├── Controllers/\n│   ├── IngestController.cs\n│   └── AskController.cs\n├── Program.cs                   # DI registration\n└── appsettings.json             # API keys, model config\n```\n\n### 6. Configuration\n- `OpenAI:ApiKey` — for embeddings + chat completion\n- `Rag:ChunkSize` (tokens), `Rag:ChunkOverlap`, `Rag:TopK`\n\n---\n\n## Trade-offs & Notes\n- **In-memory store** is fine for small doc sets; not persistent across restarts (re-ingest on startup or switch to a persistent store).\n- **Chunking by heading** preserves semantic coherence of markdown sections.\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` gives you a clean abstraction so you can swap OpenAI for Azure OpenAI / Ollama / etc. without changing business logic.\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"411a80a9-94ac-466a-9b7b-fc8f7e5c4900","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture of the project. It's a minimal .NET 10 Web API with a `Docs/` folder containing markdown files. The user wants a RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) Q&A feature plan. Let me provide a comprehensive architecture plan without writing any code.","outputTokens":1073,"requestId":"2018:52A37:89EE5A:9E7984:6A0531E4"},"id":"c1d67b3e-800f-40ed-af5b-b59c844920d6","timestamp":"2026-05-14T02:22:50.925Z","parentId":"1be934b2-98fb-434f-aaba-dd25ffca88f8"}
